		<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
			<head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
			<p>Very little is known about this item.  The manuscript is approximately 225 pages, bound in canvas; the "boards" consist of thick pads of pages recycled from other manuscripts. The title page has a large illustration of an ornate cross with textual embellishment and knotwork decoration.  The first page has a decorative border of the same knotwork.  The text, written in black and red ink, is  in the Estrangelo script of Syriac, a dialect of Aramaic. The date is unknown but is estimated to be 18th century.</p>
		</scopecontent>
		
